commitResults.messageBody: Include 1 more FindCommandState2 diagram
Attempt to include a second type of predicate to check if tags contain the keyword. To improve on the code to work more seamlessly with TagsContainKeywordsPredicate.
Refactor FindCommand to FindProjectNameCommand to more accurately capture the function's purpose of finding by project name.
Enhance original FindCommand to FindProjectNameCommand (in previous commit) and FindTagsCommand (in current commit) to support finding for a student's project by the student's tags

Add FindStudentIdCommand and FindStudentNameCommand with their parsers. FindCommand now supports four types:
1) find-n: finds for keyword in student's name
2) find-id: finds for keyword in student's id
3) find-proj: finds for keyword in student's project name
4) find-t: finds for keyword in student's tags

To do more rigorous testing and thorough checks for the tests.
Add FieldContainsKeywordsPredicate for superclass to support predicate for whether StudentId/StudentName/ProjectName/Tags contain keyword.
